*Declare a packed number variable with 7 decimal places.

REPORT Z_ABAP101_020.

*In ABAP, we can declare a packed number variable with 7 decimal places
*using the 'P' data type along with the number of decimal places specified.

DATA lv_packed_number TYPE P DECIMALS 7.

*This line declares a variable named 'lv_packed_number' of type 'P'
*(packed number) with 7 decimal places.
